KW  - Mincer equation
KW  - Linear hierarchical model
AB  - The purpose of this paper is to introduce some statistical methods for examining and comparing the coefficients from earnings functions across industries and occupations. The econometric methods introduced here have not, to our knowledge, been used to explore this question before. One technique offered here, the Lindley-Smith hyperparameter model, takes an empirical Bayes approach to estimating the parameters in a set of Mincer-type earnings equations used in the study. Since we are interested in comparing (say) the marginal return to education across occupations, the comparisons will be more meaningful if the distributions of the coefficient estimates are presumed to be from a common distribution. Once these parameters have been estimated, an appropriate technique should be used to perform the comparisons. The method used here to do this is a cluster analysis. The cluster analysis provides new information on the relative closeness of characteristics of individuals in various jobs and industries that may shed light on why differentials in estimated returns arise.
ER  - 

